main event: An unidentified flying object was reported on March 25, 1954, near Newfoundland, described as a white light in straight, level flight.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 10 seconds., The conclusion drawn was that it was probably fireball meteors., The report was part of Project 10073 under the U.S. Air Force., Major Madison G. Thomas was involved in the documentation of the sighting., The report states insufficient data for thorough evaluation.
